The paper deals with natural language processing and neural networks, which are typically associated with the computer science sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, since the focus is on morphological problems, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of neural networks suggests cs.NE as a possible sub-category, while the application to natural language processing could also justify cs.CV.
